Just sort the array and return the k-th value counting from the end:
```java
public static int findKthLargest(int[] nums, int k) {
    assert(k &gt; 0 &amp;&amp; k &lt; nums.length); // make sure k is valid
    Arrays.sort(nums);
    return nums[nums.length - k];
}
```

